00297 struct StructRNA {
00298     /* structs are containers of properties */
00299     ContainerRNA cont;
00300 
00301     /* unique identifier, keep after 'cont' */
00302     const char *identifier;
00303 
00304     /* python type, this is a subtype of pyrna_struct_Type but used so each struct can have its own type
00305      * which is useful for subclassing RNA */

00307     void *blender_type;
00308     
00309     /* various options */
00310     int flag;
00311 
00312     /* user readable name */
00313     const char *name;
00314     /* single line description, displayed in the tooltip for example */
00315     const char *description;
00316     /* context for translation */
00317     const char *translation_context;
00318     /* icon ID */
00319     int icon;
00320     
00321     /* property that defines the name */
00322     PropertyRNA *nameproperty;
00323 
00324     /* property to iterate over properties */
00325     PropertyRNA *iteratorproperty;
00326 
00327     /* struct this is derivedfrom */
00328     struct StructRNA *base;
00329 
00330     /* only use for nested structs, where both the parent and child access
00331      * the same C Struct but nesting is used for grouping properties.
00332      * The parent property is used so we know NULL checks are not needed,
00333      * and that this struct will never exist without its parent */
00334     struct StructRNA *nested;
00335 
00336     /* function to give the more specific type */
00337     StructRefineFunc refine;
00338 
00339     /* function to find path to this struct in an ID */
00340     StructPathFunc path;
00341 
00342     /* function to register/unregister subclasses */
00343     StructRegisterFunc reg;
00344     StructUnregisterFunc unreg;
00345     StructInstanceFunc instance;
00346 
00347     /* callback to get id properties */
00348     IDPropertiesFunc idproperties;
00349 
00350     /* functions of this struct */
00351     ListBase functions;
